    <p>I learned hospitality by orchestrating dining rooms where every detail carries emotional weight. I learned real estate by listening to families making the biggest commitments of their lives. Both disciplines demand trust and systems thinking. Open People Studio is how I combine that instinct with AI — proving that technology can deepen relationships instead of eroding them.</p>
    <p>The early cortex() prototypes started as service rituals written in notebooks. Today we deploy them as Operator OS modules that help people make better decisions without losing agency. The mission has not changed: expand the scope and scale of consciousness, make life multidimensional.</p>

